# Validate a mobile pin
<%= partial 'documentation/partials/google_tag_manager_js' %>

Use the GET endpoint (/api-documentation/docs/api/service/mobile-pin/1.0/oas/page#tag/mobile-pin/operation/ValidatePin) to validate the mobile pin against DOB pattern and previously used pin


## Path parameters

Parameters must be entered in lowercase.

| Parameter   | Type         | Details                       |
| -- | -- | -- |
| nino    | string       | National Insurance Number of the user         |
| enteredPin   | string       | Pin entered by the user         |


## Query parameters

| Parameter| Type | Details|
| -- | -- | -- |
| deviceId    | string       | The deviceId of the user               |
| journeyId   | string       | The journey ID of the user             |
| mode        | string       | It can either be createPin or updatePin|

[Link to Developer Hub](https://developer.service.hmrc.gov.uk)

## Responses

Full details of successful and unsuccessful responses and their schema can be found in the [API reference](//api-documentation/docs/api/service/mobile-pin/1.0/oas/page#tag/mobile-pin/operation/ValidatePin) on the HMRC Developer Hub.

| Response code | Status | Details | Contents |
| -- | -- | -- | -- |
| 200 | Successful | Successful operation | Pin Is Valid|
| 401 | Unsuccessful DOBCheck | PIN should not include your date of birth | key, message |
| 401 | Unsuccessful Previous used Pin check | Do not re-use an old PIN | key, message |
